  "page": "Battle of the Redgrass Field",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">Battle of the Redgrass Field</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Redgrass_Field.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Redgrass Field.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/64/Redgrass_Field.png/350px-Redgrass_Field.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/64/Redgrass_Field.png/525px-Redgrass_Field.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/64/Redgrass_Field.png/700px-Redgrass_Field.png 2x\" /></a><div><div style=\"width:100%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon Blackfyre</a> leads the charge during the Battle of the Redgrass Field, as depicted by Jose Daniel Cabrera Pena in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i></div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Conflict</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\nlate <a href=\"/index.php/196_AC\" title=\"196 AC\">196&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafmaekar_i_targaryen.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafmaekar_i_targaryen.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Redgrass Field\">Redgrass Field</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\nLoyalist victory</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/45px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/60px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></b> <small>(supporters of King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>)</small>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/16px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/24px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/32px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Raven%27s_Teeth\" title=\"Raven&#39;s Teeth\">Raven's Teeth</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\"><img alt=\"House Arryn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/House_Arryn.svg/16px-House_Arryn.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/House_Arryn.svg/24px-House_Arryn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/House_Arryn.svg/32px-House_Arryn.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Butterwell\" title=\"House Butterwell\"><img alt=\"House Butterwell.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/House_Butterwell.svg/16px-House_Butterwell.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/House_Butterwell.svg/24px-House_Butterwell.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/8d/House_Butterwell.svg/32px-House_Butterwell.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Butterwell\" title=\"House Butterwell\">House Butterwell</a> (supported both sides)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hayford\" title=\"House Hayford\"><img alt=\"House Hayford.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/75/House_Hayford.svg/16px-House_Hayford.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/75/House_Hayford.svg/24px-House_Hayford.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/75/House_Hayford.svg/32px-House_Hayford.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Hayford\" title=\"House Hayford\">House Hayford</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Templeton\" title=\"House Templeton\"><img alt=\"House Templeton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5b/House_Templeton.svg/16px-House_Templeton.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5b/House_Templeton.svg/24px-House_Templeton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5b/House_Templeton.svg/32px-House_Templeton.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Templeton\" title=\"House Templeton\">House Templeton</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Webber\" title=\"House Webber\"><img alt=\"House Webber.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/16/House_Webber.svg/16px-House_Webber.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/16/House_Webber.svg/24px-House_Webber.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/16/House_Webber.svg/32px-House_Webber.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Webber\" title=\"House Webber\">House Webber</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Waynwood\" title=\"House Waynwood\"><img alt=\"House Waynwood.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Waynwood.svg/16px-House_Waynwood.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Waynwood.svg/24px-House_Waynwood.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Waynwood.svg/32px-House_Waynwood.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Waynwood\" title=\"House Waynwood\">House Waynwood</a></li>\n<li>Unidentified Stormlands and Dornish houses</li></ul></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Blackfyre_2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Blackfyre 2.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/30px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/45px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/60px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b>Rebel forces/<a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackfyre\" title=\"House Blackfyre\">House Blackfyre</a></b><small>(supporters of <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon I Blackfyre</a>)</small>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\"><img alt=\"House Costayne.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/16px-House_Costayne.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/24px-House_Costayne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/69/House_Costayne.svg/32px-House_Costayne.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\">House Costayne</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\"><img alt=\"House Peake.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/16px-House_Peake.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/24px-House_Peake.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/32px-House_Peake.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Shawney\" title=\"House Shawney\"><img alt=\"House Shawney.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/House_Shawney.svg/16px-House_Shawney.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/House_Shawney.svg/24px-House_Shawney.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/House_Shawney.svg/32px-House_Shawney.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Shawney\" title=\"House Shawney\">House Shawney</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Butterwell\" title=\"House Butterwell\"><img alt=\"House Butterwell.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/House_Butterwell.svg/16px-House_Butterwell.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/House_Butterwell.svg/24px-House_Butterwell.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/8d/House_Butterwell.svg/32px-House_Butterwell.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Butterwell\" title=\"House Butterwell\">House Butterwell</a> (supported both sides)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\"><img alt=\"House Osgrey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/16px-House_Osgrey.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"18\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/24px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/32px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">House Osgrey</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor Targaryen</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar Targaryen</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/File:Brynden_Rivers.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Brynden Rivers.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Brynden_Rivers.svg/20px-Brynden_Rivers.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Brynden_Rivers.svg/30px-Brynden_Rivers.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e7/Brynden_Rivers.svg/40px-Brynden_Rivers.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Arryn.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Arryn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/House_Arryn.svg/20px-House_Arryn.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/House_Arryn.svg/30px-House_Arryn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/House_Arryn.svg/40px-House_Arryn.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Donnel_Arryn\" title=\"Donnel Arryn\">Donnel Arryn</a></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Blackfyre_2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Blackfyre 2.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/20px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/30px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a3/House_Blackfyre_2.svg/40px-House_Blackfyre_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a> King Daemon I Blackfyre<br /><a href=\"/index.php/File:Bittersteel.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Bittersteel.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/56/Bittersteel.svg/20px-Bittersteel.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/56/Bittersteel.svg/30px-Bittersteel.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/56/Bittersteel.svg/40px-Bittersteel.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Aegor_Rivers\" title=\"Aegor Rivers\">Aegor Rivers</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Unknown</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Unknown</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Casualties</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Hayford\" title=\"Lord Hayford\">Lord Hayford</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Wyl_Waynwood\" title=\"Wyl Waynwood\">Wyl Waynwood</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_Ninestars_(First_Blackfyre_Rebellion)\" title=\"Knight of Ninestars (First Blackfyre Rebellion)\">Knight of Ninestars</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Roger_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Roger of Pennytree\">Roger of Pennytree</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell's eldest son</a>†</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon I Blackfyre</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aemon Blackfyre\">Aemon Blackfyre</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aegon Blackfyre\">Aegon Blackfyre</a>†<br />Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Ball\" title=\"Quentyn Ball\">Quentyn Ball</a>†<br />Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Edwyn_Osgrey\" title=\"Edwyn Osgrey\">Edwyn Osgrey</a>†<br />Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harrold_Osgrey\" title=\"Harrold Osgrey\">Harrold Osgrey</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Osgrey\" title=\"Addam Osgrey\">Addam Osgrey</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell's second son</a>†</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Battle of the Redgrass Field</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> often simply called the <b>Redgrass Field</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> was the largest battle during the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a>, effectively ending it and confirming King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>'s rule of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#The_battle\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The battle</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>'s trueborn son and heir, <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron</a>, was born to his sister-wife <a href=\"/index.php/Naerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Naerys Targaryen\">Naerys</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_153_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">153&#160;AC</a>. Seventeen years later, Aegon's cousin, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Daena_Targaryen\" title=\"Daena Targaryen\">Daena Targaryen</a>, gave birth to the king's eldest known <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> son, <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon Waters</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_baelor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> King Aegon IV publicly acknowledged Daemon in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_182_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">182&#160;AC</a> and gave him the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> sword <a href=\"/index.php/Blackfyre\" title=\"Blackfyre\">Blackfyre</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-greatbastards_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-greatbastards-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> which had previously been passed on from king to king ever since King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>, the Conqueror. Because of this, there were some who felt that the sword symbolized the monarchy,<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and that Aegon's public gift of the sword was an indication that he wanted Daemon to succeed him. Aegon's gift would eventually start the first talks that Daemon should be king.<sup id=\"cite_ref-targaryenhistory_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-targaryenhistory-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Following the acquisition of the sword, Daemon took the name \"Blackfyre\" for himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> On his deathbed in <a href=\"/index.php/184_AC\" title=\"184 AC\">184&#160;AC</a>, King Aegon IV legitimized all of his bastard children, including Daemon.\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/196_AC\" title=\"196 AC\">196&#160;AC</a>, Daemon claimed the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>, thereby challenging his half-brother, King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The war that followed was known as the Blackfyre Rebellion (and decades later as the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a>). It lasted nigh on a year, during which time battles were fought between the rebels and loyalists in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vale\">Vale</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>, among other places.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The war came to an end after nearly a year at the <a href=\"/index.php/Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Redgrass Field\">Redgrass Field</a>. On the eve of the battle, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Ball\" title=\"Quentyn Ball\">Quentyn Ball</a>, one of Daemon's key generals, was slain by a common archer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Meanwhile, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\">Bracken</a> had gone across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a> to hire forces, but storms delayed the return of him and the <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myrish</a> crossbowmen he had hired.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_battle\">The battle</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The battle\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The two armies collided on a unnamed field. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Costayne\" title=\"House Costayne\">Costayne</a> was on the left of Daemon's host, while Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Shawney\" title=\"House Shawney\">Shawney</a> was on the right side with <a href=\"/index.php/Aegor_Rivers\" title=\"Aegor Rivers\">Aegor Rivers</a>, who was known as Bittersteel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Leo_Tyrell_(Longthorn)\" title=\"Leo Tyrell (Longthorn)\">Leo Tyrell</a>, one of Daeron's most powerful supporters, did not arrive in time for the decisive battle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Daemon was unstoppable that day, cutting Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Donnel_Arryn\" title=\"Donnel Arryn\">Donnel Arryn</a>'s van to pieces, slaying <a href=\"/index.php/Wyl_Waynwood\" title=\"Wyl Waynwood\">Wyl Waynwood</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_Ninestars_(First_Blackfyre_Rebellion)\" title=\"Knight of Ninestars (First Blackfyre Rebellion)\">Knight of Ninestars</a> before coming upon Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gwayne_Corbray\" title=\"Gwayne Corbray\">Gwayne Corbray</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>. A famous fight took place between the two with <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> swords, with Daemon wielding <a href=\"/index.php/Blackfyre\" title=\"Blackfyre\">Blackfyre</a> and Gwayne using <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Forlorn\" title=\"Lady Forlorn\">Lady Forlorn</a>, before Daemon managed to severely injure his opponent, leaving him blind and bleeding. Daemon paused then, to make sure no more injury came to Ser Gwayne, ordering <a href=\"/index.php/Redtusk\" title=\"Redtusk\">Redtusk</a> to carry Gwayne back to the <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">maesters</a> in the rear.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9f/The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/400px-The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"282\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9f/The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/600px-The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9f/The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/800px-The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Redgrass_Field_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The deaths of Daemon and his twins, by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/jota.saraiva.art/\">Jota Saraiva</a></div></div></div>\n<p>By that time, <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a>, known as Bloodraven, and his company, the <a href=\"/index.php/Raven%27s_Teeth\" title=\"Raven&#39;s Teeth\">Raven's Teeth</a>, crested the <a href=\"/index.php/Weeping_Ridge\" title=\"Weeping Ridge\">Weeping Ridge</a>, gaining the high ground from where he showered Daemon's position with arrows. Bloodraven spied Daemon's banner and slew the elder of Daemon's twin sons, <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aegon Blackfyre\">Aegon</a>, knowing that Daemon would never leave his son on the field, and then pierced Daemon with seven shafts, killing him. The younger twin, <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aemon Blackfyre\">Aemon</a>, picked up Blackfyre when his father fell, and Bloodraven slew him too.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>With their leaders fallen, the rebels began to flee then, until Bittersteel, who had commanded the right at the beginning of the battle, was able to turn the rout into a charge at the enemy. He personally fought a great battle with Bloodraven, taking his eye during a battle that was second only to Daemon and Corbray's.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> At that point, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor Breakspear</a> struck the rebel rear with a host of <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlords</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a>, shattering their lines and the battle was ended. Maekar led the rest of the forces to crush the rebels between them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Lord Shawney nearly died from his wounds, while Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell</a> lost two sons who fought on opposing sides. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Buford_Bulwer\" title=\"Buford Bulwer\">Buford Bulwer</a> allegedly killed forty men during the battle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ten thousand men died on what would later be known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Redgrass Field\">Redgrass Field</a>, presumably for all the blood sucked red.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon Blackfyre</a> and both of his eldest twin sons, <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aegon Blackfyre\">Aegon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aemon Blackfyre\">Aemon</a>, were slain in the battle, effectively ending the rebellion and confirming King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II's</a> rule of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. However, <a href=\"/index.php/Aegor_Rivers\" title=\"Aegor Rivers\">Bittersteel</a> fled to the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> with many others (including the five surviving sons and several daughters of Daemon)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackfyre_Pretenders\" title=\"Blackfyre Pretenders\">Blackfyre Pretenders</a> continued to plague the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> dynasty until <a href=\"/index.php/Maelys_Blackfyre\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maelys Blackfyre\">Maelys the Monstrous</a> was slain in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a>.\n</p><p>It is suggested that the Redgrass Field was a close thing and if Daemon had not stopped for Gwayne, he might have broken Maekar's left before Bloodraven had gained the ridge and Baelor arrived.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Then, with the Hand slain and the road to King's Landing open, Daemon would have had little opposition.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Amongst the dead were Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">Rohanne Webber</a>'s first husband, squire to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Webber\" title=\"Wyman Webber\">Wyman Webber</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Roger_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Roger of Pennytree\">Roger of Pennytree</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Arlan of Pennytree\">Arlan of Pennytree</a>'s squire;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Hayford\" title=\"Lord Hayford\">Lord Hayford</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> slain by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gormon_Peake\" title=\"Gormon Peake\">Gormon Peake</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I will never forget the way the sun looked when it set upon the <a href=\"/index.php/Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Redgrass Field\">Redgrass Field</a> ... ten thousand men had died, and the air was thick with moans and lamentations, but above us the sky turned gold and red and orange, so beautiful it made me weep to know that my sons would never see it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The singers can go on about <a href=\"/index.php/The_hammer_and_the_anvil\" title=\"The hammer and the anvil\">their hammer and their anvil</a>, ser, but it was <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">the kinslayer</a> who turned the tide with a white arrow and a <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">black spell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafmaekar_i_targaryen.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafmaekar_i_targaryen.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Maekar I Targaryen.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Daeron II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_house_tyrell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Reach: House Tyrell.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.